summary: This is an FBI request form to issue a $50.00 payment to AT&T for subscriber, billing, and call detail records related to a target phone number, as part of a grand jury investigation into obstruction of justice. The document shows law enforcement gathering financial and communication evidence.

events.title: Grand Jury Subpoena Issued to AT&T
events.description: A federal grand jury subpoena (FGJ 10-503(WPB), No. 010-018) was issued to AT&T to obtain subscriber, billing, and call detail records for a target phone number as part of an obstruction of justice investigation.

keyFacts: The FBI was investigating a case of obstruction of justice (Case ID: 72-MM-113327).
A federal grand jury subpoena was used to compel AT&T to provide subscriber, billing, and call detail records for a target phone number.
The cost for AT&T to comply with the subpoena and provide the requested records was $50.00.
The document is a routine request to issue a third-party draft to pay AT&T for the information.
